&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Summary 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Removes the default X-Requested-With header from HTTP requests made by 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; WebView.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; The X-Requested-With header is set by WebView, with the package name of 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; the embedding apk as the value. This use of the header will be 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; discontinued.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Developers who rely on this header can sign up for a deprecation origin 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; trial [1] to continue to receive the header during the deprecation period.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; The deprecation origin trial will be extended until replacement APIs 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; are available to address use cases of the header, as explained in this 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Android Developer Blog Post [2]
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; [1]: &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://developer.chrome.com/origintrials/#/view_trial/"&gt;https://developer.chrome.com/origintrials/#/view_trial/&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; 1390486384950640641
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; [2]: &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://android-developers.googleblog.com/2023/02/"&gt;https://android-developers.googleblog.com/2023/02/&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; improving-user-privacy-by-requiring-opt-in-to-send-x-
